# Supabase Configuration
# =====================
# Get these values from your Supabase project settings: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
# See SUPABASE_CONNECTION_GUIDE.md for detailed setup instructions

# Quick Start:
# - For local development: Run `npm run setup:supabase`
# - For remote setup: Follow SUPABASE_CONNECTION_GUIDE.md

# Option 1: Remote Supabase Project (Recommended for Production)
# Get these from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url-here
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Admin/Service Role Key (Server-side only - NEVER expose to client)
# Only needed for admin operations that bypass Row Level Security
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# Option 2: Local Supabase (For Development)
# Uncomment these lines and comment out the ones above if using local Supabase
# Run `npx supabase start` first, then use these values:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJleHAiOjE5ODM4MTI5OTZ9.CRXP1A7WOeoJeXxjNni43kdQwgnWNReilDMblYTn_I0
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6InNlcnZpY2Vfcm9sZSIsImV4cCI6MTk4MzgxMjk5Nn0.EGIM96RAZx35lJzdJsyH-qQwv8Hdp7fsn3W0YpN81IU

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: `cp .env.example .env.local`
# 2. For easiest setup: Run `npm run setup:supabase` (sets up local Supabase)
# 3. For remote setup: Replace the placeholder values with your Supabase credentials
# 4. Restart your dev server after updating: `npm run dev`
# 5. Test connection: Visit http://localhost:3000/test-connection
# 6. Validate setup: Run `npm run validate:supabase`

